<item>
            <title>[LU-3977] lfs quota returns ENOTSUPP after 2.1 to 2.4 server upgrade</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3977</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We recently upgraded 2.1 servers with ldiskfs backend to 2.4.  &lt;tt&gt;lfs quota&lt;/tt&gt; from a 2.1 client is now returning ENOTSUPP.  On the MDS boot messages I notice:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;LDISKFS-fs (sdb): mounted filesystem with ordered data mode. quota=off. Opts:
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Whereas before the upgrade we had:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;2013-08-17 17:29:09 LDISKFS-fs (sdb): mounted filesystem with ordered data mode. Opts:
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From digging around Jira (i.e. &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3784&quot; title=&quot;Quota issue on system upgraded to 2.4.x&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3784&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3784&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) I gather a &lt;tt&gt;tunefs.lustre --quota&lt;/tt&gt; may have been required.  But that can&apos;t be the problem, because I&apos;m sure we would never neglect to mention such an important step in the release notes or user manual.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
